%% Related: 4-2-drift-schema.mmd, 4-4-data-residency.mmd, 6-4-identification-flow.mmd, 6-5-sanctuary-donation.mmd
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> OPTIMISTIC : user action triggers optimistic UI update

    state "OPTIMISTIC" as OPTIMISTIC
    state "PENDING" as PENDING
    state "CONFIRMED" as CONFIRMED
    state "RETRYING" as RETRYING
    state "FAILED" as FAILED
    state "ROLLED_BACK" as ROLLED_BACK

    note right of OPTIMISTIC
        UI updated immediately.
        Write not yet attempted.
    end note

    note right of PENDING
        Write sent to Supabase.
        Awaiting response.
    end note

    note right of CONFIRMED
        Server acknowledged (2xx).
        Local state matches server.
    end note

    note right of RETRYING
        Write failed, will retry with
        exponential backoff (max 3 retries).
    end note

    note right of FAILED
        All retries exhausted.
        User notified.
    end note

    note right of ROLLED_BACK
        Optimistic state reverted
        due to permanent failure.
    end note

    note left of PENDING
        Idempotency: writes use WHERE guards
        e.g. WHERE identified = false
        to prevent duplicate mutations.
    end note

    OPTIMISTIC --> PENDING : network available, write dispatched
    PENDING --> CONFIRMED : server 2xx response
    PENDING --> RETRYING : network error or 5xx
    RETRYING --> PENDING : retry attempt (exponential backoff)
    RETRYING --> FAILED : max retries exceeded (3)
    FAILED --> ROLLED_BACK : rollback local state

    CONFIRMED --> [*]
    ROLLED_BACK --> [*]
